{
  "Interpreting Exponential Models": "",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "",
  "In the model P(t) = 500(1.08)^t, what is the initial value?": "",
  "In an exponential model y = a(b)^t, 'a' is the initial value. Here a = 500, representing the starting amount when t = 0.": "",
  "In the model V(t) = 20000(0.85)^t, what is the rate of decay?": "",
  "The decay factor is 0.85 = 1 - 0.15, so the rate of decay is 0.15 or 15%. The value decreases by 15% each time period.": "",
  "A population model is P(t) = 1200(1.03)^t. What is the annual growth rate?": "",
  "The growth factor is 1.03 = 1 + 0.03. The growth rate is 0.03, or 3% per year.": "",
  "A model shows N(t) = 50(2)^t. What is the value of N when t = 3?": "",
  "N(3) = 50(2)^3 = 50(8) = 400. Substitute t = 3 and evaluate the exponent first.": "",
  "A car's value is modeled by V(t) = 30000(0.82)^t. What is the car worth after 2 years?": "",
  "V(2) = 30000(0.82)^2 = 30000(0.6724) = $20,172. Each year the car retains 82% of its previous year's value.": "",
  "A model is given as f(x) = 100(3)^x. What is the growth factor and growth rate?": "",
  "The growth factor is 3 (the base). The growth rate is 3 - 1 = 2 = 200%. This means the quantity triples each period, increasing by 200% of its current value.": "",
  "An ecologist models deer population with P(t) = 120(1.08)^t and wolf population with W(t) = 30(1.12)^t. After 10 years, what is the ratio of deer to wolves? (Round to the nearest whole number.)": "",
  "P(10) = 120(1.08)^10 = 120(2.1589) = 259. W(10) = 30(1.12)^10 = 30(3.1058) = 93. Ratio = 259/93 = 2.8, approximately 3 deer per wolf.": "",
  "A real estate agent models home prices as P(t) = 350000(1.06)^t and rental costs as R(t) = 1800(1.03)^t per month. After 5 years, what is the home price and monthly rent? (Round to nearest dollar.)": "",
  "P(5) = 350000(1.06)^5 = 350000(1.338226) = $468,379 (approximately $468,381 with rounding). R(5) = 1800(1.03)^5 = 1800(1.159274) = $2,087 (rounded). Home prices grow faster (6%) than rent (3%).": "",
  "In the model A(t) = 5000(0.96)^t, what percentage of the original amount remains after 1 period?": "",
  "The decay factor 0.96 means 96% of the amount remains after each period. The other 4% is lost each period.": "",
  "A town's population is modeled by P(t) = 15000(1.04)^t, where t is years since 2020. Interpret the model: What was the population in 2020, and by what percentage does it grow each year?": "",
  "At t = 0 (year 2020), P = 15,000. The growth factor 1.04 means 1 + 0.04, so the population grows by 4% per year.": "",
  "Two cities model their populations: City A: P(t) = 50000(1.02)^t and City B: P(t) = 30000(1.05)^t. Which city is growing faster in percentage terms, and which currently has more people?": "",
  "City A starts with 50,000 people (larger) but grows at 2% per year. City B starts with 30,000 people but grows at 5% per year (faster percentage growth). Eventually City B will overtake City A.": "",
  "A company's revenue is modeled by R(t) = 250000(1.15)^t. An investor asks what the revenue will be in 3 years and what the total growth percentage is over that time.": "",
  "R(3) = 250000(1.15)^3 = 250000(1.521) = $380,172 (rounded). Total growth = (380,172 - 250,000)/250,000 = 130,172/250,000 = 0.521 = 52.1%.": ""
}